Spec: Agent Plugin Source

Purpose:
  Own shared skill templates, product plugin templates, reusable fragments, shared files, and build scripts.

Structure:
  ./skills/**: Shared skill specs and `SKILL.md.ejs` templates.
  ./plugins/**: Product-specific plugin package templates.
  ./shared/**: Shared files and assets copied into generated plugin outputs.
  ./fragments/**: Reusable rendered instruction fragments.
  ./build/**: Build scripts, product target configuration, and project-local validators.

Owns:
  ./skills/**
  ./plugins/**
  ./shared/**
  ./fragments/**
  ./build/**

Must:
  Treat source files as the editable authority for generated `../plugins/*` submodule output.
  Support Codex, Claude Code, GitHub Copilot, Junie, Cline, and Antigravity from this source tree.
  Keep shared files centralized under `./shared` or repository-level files when reused by multiple plugin targets.
  Keep target-specific package files under `./plugins/<target>`.
  Keep target rendering behavior under `./build`.
  Keep generated plugin output deterministic and committed in each plugin submodule.

Must not:
  Store marketplace-only skill behavior outside source templates.
  Duplicate shared assets or licenses in product plugin source templates.
